<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-624883 size-full lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/headies-e1571432022179.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" /> Organisers of The Headies have unveiled nominees for the Next Rated category at the 15th edition of the award show. The Headies 2022 Next Rated nominees include Bnxn, Ayra Starr, Lojay, Ruger and Zinoleesky. Back in March, organizers of The Headies awards announced a 2022 Bentley as the prize for the next Rated award category. The Headies have also unveiled nominees in other categories including: ROOKIE OF THE YEAR: BEST RECORDING OF THE YEAR PRODUCER OF THE YEAR BEST R&B SINGLE SONGWRITER OF THE YEAR BEST RAP SINGLE BEST ‘ALTERNATIVE’ SONG BEST VOCAL PERFORMANCE FEMALE BEST VOCAL PERFORMANCE MALE BEST STREET-HOP ARTISTE BEST AFROBEATS SINGLE OF THE YEAR HEADIES’ VIEWER’S CHOICE BEST WEST AFRICAN ARTISTE OF THE YEAR BEST EAST AFRICAN ARTISTE OF THE YEAR BEST NORTH AFRICAN ARTISTE OF THE YEAR BEST SOUTHERN AFRICAN ARTISTE OF THE YEAR The 15th edition of the award show is scheduled to hold at the Cobb Energy Centre Atlanta, United States, on July 12. The event’s organizers also announced new changes to the award show, such as new categories and live streaming by major TV and streaming platforms, including CNN and BBCI. The 15th Headies award show will hold for the first time outside Nigeria and will be hosted by Nancy Isime.